So  1234 is fine  but there's a case for only making these tweaks when *necessary*. & the BTC comparison doesn't convince me of necessity.
BTC can be a sanity check  but the fact is  whether ETH is secure depends little on BTC. If BTC didn't exist  ETH would still need a reward.
Most obviously - BTC reward halves every 4y. Does that mean it makes sense for ETH reward to halve  suddenly  every 4y too? Not really.
I think 1234 is fine  one of the better options. @econoar's argument for it isn't unreasonable. That said  I question the BTC comparison.
